The paper deals with quantifying synergy among stochastic variables, which is a problem in information theory. The proposed metric relies on synergistic random variables (SRVs) and has applications in biology, social cooperation processes, and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
